  • Package org.perfcake

    • Class org.perfcake.PerfCakeException extends Exception implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      7819381443289919857L

    • Class org.perfcake.RunInfo extends Object implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      2616572877123413497L

      • Serialized Fields

        • duration

          Period duration
          How long is this measurement scheduled to run in milliseconds or iterations. Another Period Types do not make any sense here.

        • startTime

          long startTime
          Unix time of the measurement start. If the system clock changes during the run, the results based on this value are influenced. The iterations however use System.nanoTime() so there is no worry.

        • endTime

          long endTime
          Unix time of the measurement end. If the system clock changes during the run, the results based on this value are influenced. The iterations however use System.nanoTime() so there is no worry.

        • scenarioName

          String scenarioName
          The name of the scenario. This can be used in reporting and is filled with scenario file name by ScenarioLoader.

      • Serialized Fields

        • iteration

          long iteration
          Iteration for which this unit was created.

        • startTime

          long startTime
          Time when last measurement started. A unit may accumulate more measurements together.

        • stopTime

          long stopTime
          Time when last measurement ended.

        • totalTime

          double totalTime
          Total measured time.

        • measurementResults

          Map<K,V> measurementResults
          Custom results reported by a sender.

        • timeStarted

          long timeStarted
          When the measurement was first started in real time (timestamp value from System.currentTimeMillis()).

        • failure

          Exception failure
          Failure that happened during processing of this task.

        • enqueueTime

          long enqueueTime
          Time when the sender request was enqueued. By default we assume this is the creation time.
